This is a textbook example of **coverage-padding** — tests that exercise every line to inflate coverage metrics while verifying almost nothing. Here's the severity-ranked audit:

---

## 🔴 Critical — Assertion-Free Tests (Coverage Without Verification)

These tests call methods but **never assert the outcome**. They pass even if the method silently does the wrong thing.

| # | Test | Bug It Misses |
|---|------|---------------|
| 1 | `AddProduct_Works` (L17-21) | Product could be silently dropped — no verification it was stored |
| 2 | `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33-35) | Price might not change — never checks the saved value |
| 3 | `RemoveProduct_Works` (L38-42) | Product may still exist after removal — no check |
| 4 | `GetProductCount_Works` (L63-66) | Result is discarded entirely — never verified |
| 5 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68-74) | Prices could be wrong after discount — never checked |
| 6 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L83-88) | Imported products never retrieved to confirm correctness |

**Fix:** Assert the *state change* or *return value*:
```csharp
// AddProduct_Works → verify round-trip
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored!.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored.Price);

// UpdatePrice_Works → verify new price
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);

// ApplyBulkDiscount_Works → verify math
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
```

---

## 🟠 High — Shallow `IsNotNull` Assertions (Trivial Assertions)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 7 | `GetProduct_Works` (L28) | Asserts non-null but never checks the returned SKU, Name, or Price |
| 8 | `SearchProducts_Works` (L51) | Asserts list is non-null but never checks count or contents |
| 9 | `GetAllProducts_Works` (L59) | Same — non-null list, no count/element check |
| 10 | `ExportToCsv_Works` (L81) | Non-null string — never checks format correctness |

**Fix:** Replace `IsNotNull` with value assertions:
```csharp
// GetProduct_Works
Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001", result!.Sku);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, result.Price);

// SearchProducts_Works
Assert.AreEqual(1, results.Count);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", results[0].Name);

